–":"1290–Overleden","1290–1352":"1290–1352","1306–Male":"1306–Overleden","1307–1347":"1307–1347","1310–1380":"1310–1380","1327–Male":"1327–Overleden","1290–Female":"1290–Overleden","1327":"1327","1347":"1347","about 1327":"circa 1327","1310":"1310","1352":"1352","1380":"1380","1307":"1307","1290":"1290","1306":"1306","Cockpool, Dumfriesshire, Scotland":"Cockpool, Dumfriesshire, Schotland","Stranith,,East Lothian,Scotland":"East Lothian, Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Angus, Perthshire, Scotland":"Angus, Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Perthshire, Scotland":"Perthshire, Schotland","Tullibardine, Blackford, Perth, Scotland":"Tullibardine, Perthshire, Schotland"},"en":{"1290–":"1290–Deceased","1290–1352":"1290–1352","1306–Male":"1306–Deceased","1307–1347":"1307–1347","1310–1380":"1310–1380","1327–Male":"1327–Deceased","1290–Female":"1290–Deceased","1327":"1327","1347":"1347","about 1327":"about 1327","1310":"1310","1352":"1352","1380":"1380","1307":"1307","1290":"1290","1306":"1306","Cockpool, Dumfriesshire, Scotland":"Cockpool, Dumfriesshire, Scotland","Stranith,,East Lothian,Scotland":"East Lothian, Scotland, United Kingdom","Angus, Perthshire, Scotland":"Angus, Scotland, United Kingdom","Perthshire, Scotland":"Perthshire, Scotland","Tullibardine, Blackford, Perth, Scotland":"Tullibardine, Perthshire, Scotland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Randolf","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English and German: variant of   Randolph  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Randolph","meanings":["English and German: from <i>Randolf</i>, an ancient Germanic personal name composed of the elements <i>rand</i> ‘rim (of a shield), shield’ + <i>wolf</i> ‘wolf’. This was introduced into England by the Normans in Old French forms of two different ancient Germanic personal names which became confused with each other: <i>Randulf</i> (from <i>rand</i> ‘(shield-)edge’ + <i>wulf</i> ‘wolf’) and <i>Rannulf</i> (from <i>hraf(a)n</i> ‘raven’ + <i>wulf</i> ‘wolf’).","History: An American family bearing this surname are descended from William Randolph (<i>c.</i> 1651–1711), a planter and merchant, a member of a family that originally came from Sussex, England. William Randolph emigrated from Warwickshire to VA <i>c.</i> 1673. He was a forebear of Thomas Jefferson and Robert E. Lee. Randolph had seven sons, each of whom inherited an estate, the name of which was sometimes added to their own, such as Sir John Randolph of Tazewell. His great-grandsons included Edmund Randolph (1753–1813), first attorney general of the US and one of the framers of the US Constitution, and the diplomat and statesman John Randolph of Roanoke (1773–1833), who served as US minister to Russia."]}]},{"name":"Mabel","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a nickname from the Old French vocabulary word <i>amabel</i>, <i>amable</i> ‘lovely’ (akin to modern English <i>amiable</i> ‘friendly, good-humoured’). The initial vowel began to be lost as early as the 12th century (the same woman is referred to as both <i>Mabilia</i> and <i>Amabilia</i> in a document of  1185 ), but a short vowel in the resulting first syllable was standard, giving a rhyme with <i>babble</i>, until the 19th century, when people began to pronounce the name to rhyme with <i>table</i>."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Isabella","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of   Isabel  , which has been popular in England since the 18th century and has recently become the preferred form of the name."],"variants":[{"name":"Isobella","meanings":["form of   Isabel  , which has been popular in England since the 18th century and has recently become the preferred form of the name."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Mabel Isabella Randolf was born in 1290, in Angus, Scotland, United Kingdom. She had at least 3 sons and 1 daughter with William Murray - III Laird of Tullibardine."},"et":{"1290–":"1290–Surnud","1290–1352":"1290–1352","1306–Male":"1306–Surnud","1307–1347":"1307–1347","1310–1380":"1310–1380","1327–Male":"1327–Surnud","1290–Female":"1290–Surnud","1327":"1327","1347":"1347","about 1327":"umbes 1327","1310":"1310","1352":"1352","1380":"1380","1307":"1307","1290":"1290","1306":"1306","Cockpool, Dumfriesshire, Scotland":"Cockpool, Dumfriesshire, Scotland","Stranith,,East Lothian,Scotland":"East Lothian, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Angus, Perthshire, Scotland":"Angus, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Perthshire, Scotland":"Perthshire, Scotland","Tullibardine, Blackford, Perth, Scotland":"Tullibardine, Perthshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"1290–":"1290–Kuollut","1290–1352":"1290–1352","1306–Male":"1306–Kuollut","1307–1347":"1307–1347","1310–1380":"1310–1380","1327–Male":"1327–Kuollut","1290–Female":"1290–Kuollut","1327":"1327","1347":"1347","about 1327":"noin 1327","1310":"1310","1352":"1352","1380":"1380","1307":"1307","1290":"1290","1306":"1306","Cockpool, Dumfriesshire, Scotland":"Cockpool, Dumfriesshire, Scotland","Stranith,,East Lothian,Scotland":"East Lothian, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Angus, Perthshire, Scotland":"Angus, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Perthshire, Scotland":"Perthshire, Scotland","Tullibardine, Blackford, Perth, Scotland":"Tullibardine, Perthshire, Scotland"},"fr":{"1290–":"1290–Décédée","1290–1352":"1290–1352","1306–Male":"1306–Décédé","1307–1347":"1307–1347","1310–1380":"1310–1380","1327–Male":"1327–Décédé","1290–Female":"1290–Décédée","1327":"1327","1347":"1347","about 1327":"environ 1327","1310":"1310","1352":"1352","1380":"1380","1307":"1307","1290":"1290","1306":"1306","Cockpool, Dumfriesshire, Scotland":"Cockpool, Dumfriesshire, Écosse","Stranith,,East Lothian,Scotland":"East Lothian, Écosse, Royaume-Uni","Angus, Perthshire, Scotland":"Angus, Écosse, Royaume-Uni","Perthshire, Scotland":"Perthshire, Écosse","Tullibardine, Blackford, Perth, Scot